This doesn't really come alive until the last paragraph, some entries on the list are nice and everything works well as setup. But you can only build up for so long, and a piece like this demands a lot more character than it currently has to meet its full potential. William Plunkett's fate could've been a through-line to build an article around but instead it's a very well-done but far too brief ending which only made me go back and realize how much better this SCP could be.








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






